st%20year%20or%20so%2C%20but%202024%20will%20be%20a%20baby%20step%20in%20the%20right%20direction%2C%26quot%3B%20Chief%20Economist%20Danielle%20Hale%20said%20in%20the%20report.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20going%20to%20stop%20getting%20worse.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMortgage%20rates%20decline%2C%20home%20prices%20dip%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBorrowing%20costs%20will%20fall%20somewhat%2C%20as%20easing%20labor%20and%20inflation%20data%20prompt%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20to%20turn%20dovish.%20That's%20after%20the%2030-year%20mortgage%20rate%20soared%20this%20year%2C%20briefly%20breaching%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcommodities%2Fhousing-market-fixed-mortgage-outlook-home-prices-rates-interest-fed-2023-10%5C%22%3E8%25%20in%20October%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20while%20some%20see%20a%20drop%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-outlook-home-prices-rental-supply-competition-mortgage-rates-2023-11%5C%22%3Eas%20low%20as%205%25%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Realtor.com%20sees%20an%20average%20of%206.8%25%2C%20compared%20to%207.22%25%20in%20Freddie%20Mac's%20latest%20survey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20this%20will%20be%20enough%20to%20take%20pressure%20off%20buyers%2C%20who%20won't%20feel%20rushed%20to%20buy%20before%20rates%20rise%20further.%20Demand%20should%20slow%2C%20with%20home%20prices%20dropping%201.7%25.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETogether%20with%20smaller%20mortgage%20payments%20and%20expectations%20for%20income%20growth%20next%20year%2C%20the%20share%20of%20a%20household's%20income%20required%20for%20a%20mortgage%20payment%20should%20slip%20to%2030%25%20by%20the%20end%20of%202024%20from%20this%20year's%20average%20of%2036.7%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20not%20a%20seismic%20decline%2C%20the%20housing%20market%20has%20rapidly%20grown%20more%20expensive%20since%202020.%20To%20afford%20a%20home%2C%20Americans%20must%20now%20make%20a%20record%20%24114%2C627%20a%20year%2C%20an%20%3Ca%20href%