%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Friday%20said%20a%20governor%20cannot%20refer%20to%20the%20president%20Bills%20that%20they%20have%20previously%20withheld%20assent%20to%2C%20advising%C2%A0Tamil%20Nadu%20governor%20R.N.%20Ravi%20to%20resolve%20the%20impasse%20with%20the%20state%20government%20over%2010%20Bills.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Fjudiciary%2Fcant-withhold-assent-then-refer-to-president-sc-asks-tn-governor-to-resolve-impasse-over-bills%2F1867039%2F%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Print%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20three-judge%20bench%20led%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20made%20the%20verbal%20suggestion%20to%20attorney%20general%20R.%20Venkataramani.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERavi%20had%20withheld%20assent%20to%2010%20Bills%2C%20that%20pertained%20to%20modifications%20in%20state%20university%20laws%2C%20which%20the%20legislature%20passed%20again%20without%20any%20amendments%20but%20later%20referred%20them%20to%20the%20President%2C%20just%20days%20after%20the%20top%20court%20questioned%20the%20governor%20for%20sitting%20on%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20November%2013%2C%20the%20governor%20said%20he%20had%20withheld%20his%20assent%20to%20the%2010%20Bills%2C%20which%20also%20took%20away%20the%20governor%E2%80%99s%20powers%2C%20as%20chancellor%20of%20state%20universities%2C%20to%20appoint%20vice-chancellors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESubsequently%2C%20the%20state%20assembly%20convened%20a%20special%20session%20on%20November%2018%20and%20passed%20them%20again.%20On%20November%2020%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20asked%20the%20governor%20about%20the%20pending%20Bills.%20On%20November%2028%2C%20the%20governor%20referred%20them%20to%20the%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Print%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20CJI%20Chandrachud%20said%20on%20Friday%20that%20under%20Article%20200%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20the%20governor%20has%20only%20three%20options%20%E2%80%94%20grant%20assent%2C%20withhold%20assent%20or%20refer%20it%20to%20the%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20%E2%80%9Calternatives%E2%80%9D%20and%20once%20he%20has%20withheld%20assent%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthere%20is%20no%20question%20of%20him%20referring%20them%20to%20the%20president%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20CJI%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20stressed%20once%20again%20that%20the%20proviso%20of%20Article%20200%20does%20not%20allow%20the%20governor%20to%20stall%20a%20Bill%20once%20it%20is%20re-enacted%20by%20the%20assembly.%20CJI%20Chandrachud%20referred%20to%20the%20top%20court%E2%80%99s%20verdict%20on%20November%2010%20concerning%20the%20Punjab%20governor%E2%80%99s%20delay%C2%A0in%20assenting%20to%20certain%20Bills.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fsc-says-no-question-of-tamil-nadu-governor-referring-10-re-enacted-bills-to-president-now%2Farticle67593997.ece%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Tamil%20Nadu%20government%20told%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Friday%20that%20Ravi%20was%20exhibiting%20%E2%80%9Cconstitutional%20obstinacy%E2%80%9D%20by%20referring%20the%2010%20re-enacted%20Bills%20to%20the%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAG%C2%A0Venkataramani%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20argued%20that%20the%20governor%20had%20%E2%80%9Csimply%20withheld%20assent%E2%80%9D%20on%20November%2013%20and%20did%20not%20send%20them%20back.%20%E2%80%9CNow%2C%20this%20was%20not%20a%20case%20when%20the%20Governor%20had%20asked%20the%20Assembly%20to%20reconsider%20the%20Bills%20or%20had%20recommended%20changes.%20Here%2C%20he%20had%20only%20communicated%20to%20the%20Assembly%20on%20November%2013%20that%20he%20had%20withheld%20assent%E2%80%A6%20The%20Bills%20were%20not%20technically%20sent%20back%20to%20the%20Assembly%20for%20reconsideration%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20argued%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSo%2C%20you%20are%20saying%20the%20